## Appendix B: Complete Parsing Algorithm (Pseudocode)

```
function parse_event_stream(stream):
    data_buffer = ""
    event_type_buffer = ""
    last_event_id_buffer = ""

    decode stream as UTF-8 (stripping leading BOM if present)

    for each line in stream (split on CR LF | CR | LF):

        if line is empty:
            dispatch_event(data_buffer, event_type_buffer, last_event_id_buffer)
            data_buffer = ""
            event_type_buffer = ""
            // last_event_id_buffer is NOT reset

        else if line starts with ':':
            // comment; ignore

        else if line contains ':':
            field = substring before first ':'
            value = substring after first ':'
            if value starts with ' ' (U+0020):
                value = value[1:]  // remove first character only
            process_field(field, value)

        else:
            // line has no colon
            process_field(line, "")

    // End of stream: discard any pending data (no dispatch)


function process_field(field, value):
    if field == "event":
        event_type_buffer = value

    else if field == "data":
        data_buffer += value
        data_buffer += '\n'  // U+000A

    else if field == "id":
        if '\0' not in value:  // U+0000 NULL not present
            last_event_id_buffer = value

    else if field == "retry":
        if value matches /^[0-9]+$/:
            reconnection_time = parse_int(value)

    else:
        // ignore unknown fields


function dispatch_event(data_buffer, event_type_buffer, last_event_id_buffer):
    // Update the event source's last event ID string
    event_source.last_event_id = last_event_id_buffer

    if data_buffer == "":
        return  // do not fire an event

    // Strip trailing LF
    if data_buffer ends with '\n':
        data_buffer = data_buffer[:-1]

    // Determine event type
    event_type = event_type_buffer if event_type_buffer != "" else "message"

    // Create the event
    event = new Event(
        type = event_type,
        data = data_buffer,
        lastEventId = event_source.last_event_id,
        origin = final_url_origin
    )

    // Queue for delivery with readyState guard:
    // At delivery time (not now), check if still open
    queue_task(function():
        if event_source.readyState != CLOSED:
            deliver(event)
        // else: silently drop
    )
```

